.SH NAME
HTMLInputElement.capture \- HTMLInputElement: capture property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]capture\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLInputElement\f[R] interface reflects the \f[CR]<input>\f[R]
element\[cq]s \f[CR]capture\f[R] attribute.
Only relevant to the \f[CR]<input>\f[R] of type \f[CR]file\f[R], the
property and attribute specify whether, a new file should be captured
from a user\-facing (\f[CR]user\f[R]) or outward facing
(\f[CR]environment\f[R]) camera or microphone.
The type of file is defined the \f[CR]accept\f[R] attribute.
If the attribute is not explicitly set, the \f[CR]capture\f[R] property
is an empty string.
.SH VALUE
A string; Generally either \f[CR]user\f[R] or \f[CR]environment\f[R], or
an empty string (\f[CR]\[dq]\[dq]\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] inputElement = document.querySelector(\[dq]avatar\[dq]);
console.log(inputElement.capture); \f[I]// the current value of the capture attribute\f[R]
inputElement.capture = \[dq]user\[dq]; \f[I]// sets the capture value\f[R]
.EE
